social_posts.post_text: Settling into the holidays with wifey/adventure queen @siouxzen . Plenty of holiday adventures, music and crafts ahead of us. Tonight’s craft, stringing/eating popcorn on the couch while watching a holiday movie....ahhh the simple things.

As you all know I am an actor by profession and when I’m not working on a project I have the privilege of teaching this art-form to beginners of all ages. Teaching is one of the most enjoyable jobs I have ever had and to be able to help an actor through the beginning steps/stages of their journey is truly rewarding.

If you or someone you know wants to become an actor, is a working actor or simply wants to take a glimpse into what it takes to be an actor, I encourage you to check out my Holiday Coaching Deals!

I have priced these coaching sessions to be extremely competitive and affordable....based on the prices I have personally paid to be coached. And yes, from time to time, I still need help/direction on auditions/projects that I’m working on. Process is forever!

These sessions are catered specifically to the needs to the actor SO whether they need help in Scene Study, Audition Prep., Commercial and Monologue Work OR Self Tape Help....these deals are a great fit!

If you have any questions at all feel free to reach out! Have a lovely Holiday Season and a very happy New Year!

All the love,
Chris

As proof that we are still alive and active, here is a lovely photo of @siouxzen myself and Momma Kang on Christmas....oh and Penny. We had a lovely, slow, Holiday Season. I soaked it up because this year is going to be busy....I know it. Speaking of.....Happy New Years everyone! All I can say is I’m ready for this year. This year will change us all in ways we couldn’t possibly imagine. Stay the course. Choose growth. Work hard. Live within the truth of your actions. Love beyond limits. Be kind to those you come in contact with. Be kind to yourself. Keep your eyes wide, your ears open and your mind sharp. You have been training your whole life for this year....get after it. Stay hungry. Stay open, gentle and generous. This year is for the top glass of the champagne tower. May the blessings flow to you, fill you up and overflow into the world around you. Spread the love and the wealth. Sending you all love. Thanks for taking this ride with me. Thank you for your support. Be well! See you out there!!!!

All the love,
Chris

Just finished up my latest demo “Let You In” right in time for a Valentine’s Day release! This song is about contemplating whether or not you should dive head first into love. It’s scary, it’s exciting, it kinda makes you nauseous but when you find the right person....the only real choice is to let them in. Buy it / Stream It / Send it to a lover/crush....do what you do. As always, thanks for the love and support!

All the love,
Chris

Happy Valentine’s Day world! Made a little art with some friends for you to enjoy today. This is my latest demo/video for my song “Let You In”. Link in bio to watch the whole film. Let me know what you think!

Be well!
Chris

Mia was my adventure partner. Adopting her was an active choice I made 14 years ago to start growing up and taking responsibility for another living being other than myself. She taught me so much. She chose me and I’m eternally grateful for that. She will be missed but I rest easy knowing she had an amazing life and she was LOVEDDDDDDDD. She was cherished. Thanks for choosing me Mia....you will always be in my heart and will forever be my favorite little fluffy puppy.

Hello world! I just added a new Saturday Morning Scene Study Class for ages 13-18 every Saturday at 11am PST! As of now most of my students tend to be beginners ages 7-18 so my classes are catered toward that age group HOWEVER should you be 18+ and interested in the art form of acting I would absolutely create a new class for adults who are interested. I also offer 30 minute and 1 hour private coaching for those students who work better with one-on-one attention. If you have any questions at all send me a message! I’ll also be adding more classes in the coming days so stay tuned!

Have a beautiful week everyone!

All the love,
Chris

Hello world,
I have decided to start releasing stripped down versions of my songs. My intention was to wait until they are properly recorded, until I had the time and money to manifest them to the best of their/my ability. I wanted you to hear them for the first time when they are “done”....or “perfect” but time flies, money is tight and life is short. So until I have that luxury I will offer up the art that exists closest to my heart in the way that it first comes into existence....with just me and a guitar. 

I write these songs for me and I write them for you. I create them from a space of connection, hoping that one day we can sing them together. 

If you have read this far and if you listen to “Weary” THANK YOU. Sending allllll the love your way.

Be well fam and when you’re down and feeling weary ....remember to listen to that still/small voice that tells you, “Don’t worry your head about it”. All will work out in the end.

Your friend,
Chris

Whatcha know about family?!?! We had such an amazing weekend together adventuring/connecting/laughing/eating and just loving up on each other. I love these humans and I cannot wait to see what next year holds for all of us. Big things are brewing....this I can promise you.

Actors! 2024 is our year! Now is the time to put in the work so that we can show up to the best of our ability in every opportunity that this year/industry sends our way. If you are looking for a safe creative place to grow within this art form you have come to the right place! I offer group classes 3 days a week and private 1-on-1 coaching sessions (great for self tapes) that range from 30 minutes to 1 hour! You can book through the link in my bio and if you have any questions at all do not hesitate to reach out! 

“Luck is what happens when preparation meets opportunity”…..so let’s stay ready. 

All the best,
Chris
Actor / Musician / Student / Teacher
